{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox project | name = Billion Tree Tsunami | image = Billion Tree Tsunami Logo.png | caption= Logo | location = Pakistan: [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Pakistan|Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] | key_people = [[Imran khan]] | established = {{Start date|2014}} | website = {{URL|103.240.220.71/btt/}} |country=[[Pakistan]]}}
The '''Billion Tree Tsunami''' was launched in 2014, by the government of [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] (KPK), Pakistan, as a response to the challenge of [[global warming]]. Pakistan’s Billion Tree Tsunami restores 350,000 hectares of forests and degraded land to surpass its [[Bonn Challenge]] commitment.<ref name="iucn">{{cite web|title=Pakistan’s Billion Tree Tsunami restores 350,000 hectares of forests and degraded land to surpass Bonn Challenge commitment|url=https://www.iucn.org/news/forests/201708/pakistan%E2%80%99s-billion-tree-tsunami-restores-350000-hectares-forests-and-degraded-land-surpass-bonn-challenge-commitment|publisher=[[International Union for Conservation of Nature]]|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref name="bc">{{cite web|title=Pakistan (KPK)|url=http://www.bonnchallenge.org/content/pakistan-kpk|website=Bonn Challenge|publisher=[[International Union for Conservation of Nature]]|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> The project aimed at improving the ecosystems of classified forests, as well as privately owned waste and farm lands, and therefore entails working in close collaboration with concerned communities and stakeholders to ensure their meaningful participation through effectuating project promotion and extension services.<ref name="gkp">{{cite web|title=About Billion Tree Tsunami Afforestation Project|url=http://few.kp.gov.pk/page/about_billion_tree_tsunami_afforestation_project|publisher=[[Government of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]]|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> The projected was completed in August 2017, ahead of schedule.<ref>{{cite web|last= Hutt | first= Rosamond |url=https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2018/07/pakistan-s-billion-tree-tsunami-is-astonishing/|title=Pakistan has planted over a billion trees|website=World Economic Forum |date=July 2, 2018}}</ref>
==Inspiration== The Billion Tree Tsunami Project is driven by the [[Government of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]]’s vision of green growth which ties in the needs for sustainable forestry development, generating green jobs, gender empowerment, preserving Pakistan’s [[natural capital]] while also addressing the global issue of climate change.<ref>{{cite web|title=Billion Tree Tsunami Afforestation Project – Country's largest plantation drive|url=http://103.240.220.71/btt/|publisher=Forestry, Environment & Wildlife Department, KP|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref>
==Afforestation Regions== The Billion Tree Tsunami covers the whole province of KPK. {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! Region !! Division |- | Central-Southern Forest Region-I [[Peshawar]] || *[[Forest Division D.I.Khan]] *[[Forest Division Bannu]] *[[Forest Division Kohat]] *[[Forest Division Peshawar]] *[[Forest Division Mardan]] |- | Northern Forest Region-II [[Abbottabad]] || *[[Forest Division Haripur]] *[[Forest Division Agror Tanawal]] *[[Forest Division Tor Ghar]] *[[Forest Division Gallies]] *[[Forest Division Siran]] *[[Forest Division Kaghan]] *[[Forest Division Hazara Tribal]] *[[Forest Division Lower Kohistan]] *[[Forest Division Upper Kohistan]] *[[Forest Division Daur Watershed]] *[[Forest Division Kohistan Watershed]] *[[Forest Division Unhar Watershed]] *[[Forest Division Kunhar Watershed]] *[[Forest Division Buner Watershed]] |- | Northern Forest Region-III [[Malakand District|Malakand]] || *[[Forest Division Malakand]] *[[Forest Division Buner]] *[[Forest Division Lower Dir]] *[[Forest Division Swat]] *[[Forest Division Alpuri]] *[[Forest Division Kalam]] *[[Forest Division Upper Dir]] *[[Forest Division Dir Kohistan]] *[[Forest Division Chitral]] |}
==10 Billion Tree Tsunami==
On 3rd September, 2018, Imran Khan launched a 5 year, country-wide 10 billion tree plantation drive from Makhniyal, [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa|KPK]] to combat the effects of global warming.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/03-Sep-2018/10-billion-tree-tsunami-drive-launched|title=10 Billion Tree Tsunami drive launched|date=3 September 2018|publisher=The Nation}}</ref>
